Holy Priest Mythic+ Guide

11.0.7 - The War Within

Last Updated:December 18, 2024|Changelog|FAQ

Welcome to the Holy Priest Mythic+ guide for the World of Warcraft patch 11.0.2! This guide covers everything you need to know to understand your character! Are you starting out and leveling up from 70? Check out the leveling guide!

Hero Talents

Patch 11.0.7 - The War Within
Holy Priest
  • Archon     focuses on your constant healing output, while
    Oracle     focuses on enhancing your big healing cooldowns and providing utility to the team.
Archon
Oracle
  • When casting
    Halo     you also periodically create more Halos that return to you. They are enhanced by the following nodes and grant you certain benefits:
    • Power Surge
      • Creates multiple
        Halos        .
    • Resonant Energy
      • Applies an increased healing taken buff to any ally hit by a
        Halo         ring.
    • Energy Compression
      • massively increases the effectiveness of each
        Halo        .
    • Divine Halo
      • Halos         return to you after reaching max distance.
  • Oracle     grants you a new Ability that cycles through 4 different versions:
    1. Premonition of Insight
      • Decreases the cooldown of the next 3 spells you cast by 7 seconds.
    2. Premonition of Piety
      • Increases your healing done by a large amount and causes 70% of your overhealing to be redistributed.
    3. Premonition of Solace
      • Your next
        Flash Heal        ,
        Heal        ,
        Holy Word: Serenity         or
        Renew         apply a massive absorb and a 15% dr to your target.
    4. Premonition of Clairvoyance
      • Gain the effects of all the other
        Premonitions        .

Talents

Patch 11.0.7 - The War Within
Holy Priest
General Talent Build

When to use this Spec

This is the default loadout going into any dungeon. You need to adjust class talent tree based on the utility needed for the affix and dungeon combo. To make your life easier, Dungeon specific talent loadouts are available in the Dungeon section.

Gameplay Altering Talents

Discover all talents that significantly alter your gameplay within the Spec and Class Talent trees. This section gives a concise overview of these talents and their applications but for a more detailed look check out the Rotation and Deep Dive sections below.

Spec Tree

  • Voice of Harmony
    • This crucial talent restores harmony to the flow of your healing rotation as it allows
      Prayer of Mending       and
      Holy Fire       to reduce the cooldown of your Holy Word spells, exactly like all your other core rotational spells.
  • Lightweaver
    • This talent changes your rotation in a way that you are casting
      Heal       as an emergency spell, as it does the most healing and has a short cast time.
  • Trail of Light
    • An important talent to utilize, as it introduces a new mechanic to the class by turning your
      Flash Heal       and
      Heal       into multi target spells. You need to think about whom you target with your Flash Heal and Heal, and in which order, as they also heal your previous target.
  • Empyreal Blaze
    • The talent significantly increases the amount of
      Holy Fires       you can cast during a dungeon and offers a way to keep up your damage while moving, since the extra
      Holy Fires       are instant.
  • Burning Vehemence
    • Transforms
      Holy Fire       into your most powerful damage spell in any scenario, allowing you to add meaningful damage in AoE pulls.
  • Miracle Worker
    • Enables you to prepare effectively for critical moments by granting you an additional charge of your healing Holy Words. This greatly enhances the value of the Holy Priest's core cooldown reduction mechanic, as you can now retain one charge for emergencies.
  • Guardian Angel
    • Enables you to use
      Guardian Spirit       more frequently, greatly easing difficult encounters.
  • Divine Image
    • Rewards you for planning ahead with your Holy Words. The Naaru is empowered by each Holy Word you cast, but the empowerment only lasts for a short duration.

Class Tree

  • Phantom Reach
    • Increases the range of your spells to 46 yards, giving you a significant advantage. This allows you to outrange certain Mythic+ mechanics or continue healing your teammates even if the party spreads out.
  • Surge of Light
    • This talent significantly helps with mana management and mobility, providing you with an additional recovery tool while on the move.
  • Twins of the Sun Priestess
    • You also gain the effects of
      Power Infusion       when you cast it on an ally.
  • Protective Light
    • In combination with
      Binding Heal       and
      Surge of Light      , this talent provides you with an easily accessible 10% damage reduction.
  • Translucent Image
    • Adds a new but weak defensive ability to the Priest class toolkit. However, when combined with
      Protective Light      , it could save your life!
  • Rhapsody
    • This talent turns Holy Nova into a small AoE damage cooldown, but it requires you to be in melee range, so use it cautiously.

Hero Talent Tree

  • Incessant Screams
    • Your Fear recasts after a short duration stopping all casts again.
  • Word of Supremacy
    • Only Increases the amount of stamina you gain from your Class buff.

Rotation

Patch 11.0.7 - The War Within
Holy Priest

Tier Set

  • 2-Set: 
    Serendipity     is 10% more effective.
  • 4-Set: 
    Heal    ,
    Flash Heal     and
    Prayer of Healing     have a 50% chance to cast again at 35% effectiveness.

Priority List

For Healing

  1. Cast
    Prayer of Mending     on Cooldown.
  2. Cast
    Heal     if
    Resonant Words     and
    Lightweaver     are active.
  3. Cast
    Holy Word: Serenity     if at 2 charges and you do not have
    Resonant Words     active.
  4. Cast 
    Holy Word: Sanctify     on Cooldown if there is AoE healing to be done, people are stacked, and you do not have
    Resonant Words     active.
  5. Cast
    Flash Heal     to generate
    Lightweaver     stacks.
  6. Cast 
    Holy Word: Serenity     if people require enough single target healing and you do not have
    Resonant Words     active.
  7. Cast
    Holy Nova     if you have 15 or more stacks of
    Rhapsody     and there is AoE healing to be done and people are stacked.
  8. Cast
    Heal     to reduce the Cooldown of
    Holy Word: Serenity    .
  9. Cast
    Renew     on movement globals. (Skip this if you run into mana issues)

For Damage

  1. Cast 
    Holy Fire     on Cooldown
  2. Cast 
    Holy Word: Chastise     on Cooldown
  3. Cast 
    Holy Nova     if at max stacks
  4. Cast 
    Holy Nova     if 5 or more targets.
  5. Cast
    Smite
  6. Multi-DoT with 
    Shadow Word: Pain     on movement globals

Cooldowns

Halo

  • As archon holy priest
    Halo     becomes your main cooldown make sure to position properly and always be aware that you need to take advantage of the massive damage this spell does as well.

Divine Hymn

  • With the recent changes to
    Divine Hymn     scaling within dungeons, it has become a potent cooldown. Maximizing this cooldown is all about making use of the increased healing taken buff on the group afterwards!

Apotheosis

  • Apotheosis     is your biggest output cooldown for both damage and healing. Use it as often as possible to reset the cooldowns of your Holy Words and save Mana. During
    Apotheosis    , prioritize casting
    Flash Heal    , as it reduces the cooldown of
    Holy Word: Serenity     the most.

Deep Dive

Patch 11.0.7 - The War Within
Holy Priest

Lightweaver

  • Properly minmaxing this talent increases not only your direct healing output but also the amount of Holy Words you can cast over the course of a dungeon. Try to make playing this talent a habit of yours, so you don't have to constantly think about it since this is a pretty simple talent.

Optimizing
Power Infusion

  • While
    Power Infusion     is your spell, the optimal usage is to prioritize your teammates' benefit over your own. To achieve this, track your party members' offensive cooldown uptime. It is recommended to use addons or WeakAuras for this, as discussed in the Addon section, or simply communicate with your teammates and ask them to request it at the exact time they need it.

Understanding Mechanics

Rotational min-maxing is just one aspect of mastering a specialization, but there are numerous other key mechanics that influence your performance. Use the following guides to improve them.

  • Pandemic
  • Spell Queue Window
  • Stat Diminishing Returns

Boss Tips

Avanoxx

  • General Tips
    • Always dispel
      Web Wrap       targets instantly.
  • Output Cds
    • Always tie your Cooldowns to
      Gossamer Onslaught       as this is the event that does the most damage.
  • Personal/External
    • Ensure to always have both
      Protective Light       and
      Fade       active when
      Alerting Shrill       or
      Gossamer Onslaught       is happening.
    • Use
      Algari Healing Potion       as the first line of emergency defensives, whenever you drop to low HP.

Anub'zekt

  • General Tips
    • Always stay close to the boss as it otherwise becomes harder to dodge
      Impale       the further away you are.
  • Output Cds
    • Rotate through your healing arsenal to heal through the damage done by
      Infestation      .
  • Personal/External
    • Fill the spaces between your healing cooldowns by using defensives and communicating to your group to do the same.

Ki'katal the Harvester

  • General Tips
    • Get rid of
      Grasping Blood       with
      Psychic Scream       when
      Cosmic Singularity       cast finishes.
  • Personal/External
    • Rotate through your defensive arsenal whenever you are affected by
      Cultivated Poisons      .

Trash Tips

  • Important abilities to interrupt in this dungeon are:
    • Trilling Attendant -
      Resonant Barrage
    • Ixin -
      Horrifying Shrill
    • Bloodstained Webmage -
      Revolting Volley
    • Blood Overseer -
      Venom Volley
  • Pay extra attention to these casts:
    • Sentry Stagshell -
      Alarm Shrill
      • A really long cast that needs to get disrupted.
    • Nerubian Hauler and Hulking Bloodguard -
      Massive Slam
      • A short stun that ramps in damage done per cast.
    • Nakt -
      Call of the Brood
      • Massive amount of damage to all players.

Boss Tips

Orator Krix'vizk

  • General Tips
    • Your Group needs to ensure that they are spread for
      Shadows of Doubt      , so you can instantly dispel one debuff.
      Mass Dispel       can come in handy here as well.
  • Output Cds
    • The boss casts
      Vociferous Indoctrination       every 32 seconds making it very easy for you to have multiple Holy Words ready each time.
  • Personal/External
    • On higher keys, always use a defensive and have both
      Protective Light       and
      Fade       active when you tank
      Shadows of Doubt       for its full duration.

Fangs of the Queen

  • General Tips
    • Stack in melee to instantly remove
      Freezing Blood      .
  • Output Cds
    • Always ensure to have a healing cooldowns ready when
      Ice Sickles       happens.
  • Personal/External
    • Whenever
      Knife Throw       overlaps with
      Ice Sickles       use a personal and have both
      Protective Light       and
      Fade       active.

The Coaglamation

  • General Tips
    • Viscous Darkness       knocks you. Make sure to not be knocked into an already existing pool!
  • Output Cds
    • Rotate through your healing cooldowns and fill gaps with Pots and Raid Cooldowns from your party as this boss has a constant high HPS requirement.
  • Personal/External
    • Ensure to have a personal defensive active when
      Dark Pulse       happens. This happens every 70 seconds so you need to alternate between
      Guardian Spirit       and
      Desperate Prayer      .

Izo, the Grand Splicer

  • General Tips
    • Stay stacked with your group, do not bait
      Shifting Anomalies       ahead.
  • Output Cds
    • Only use holy words when
      Splice       is active.
    • Rotate through your different healing cooldowns and potions for every set of
      Splice       as it is followed up by either
      Tremor Slam       or
      Umbral Weave      , which is a very lethal combination.
  • Personal/External
    • Ensure to have both
      Protective Light       and
      Fade       active whenever
      Tremor Slam       or
      Umbral Weave       happens.

Trash Tips

  • Important abilities to interrupt in this dungeon are:
    • Sureki Silkbinder -
      Silk Binding
    • Herald of Ansurek -
      Twist Thoughts
    • Covert Webmancer -
      Mending Web
  • Pay extra attention to these casts:
    • Eye of the Queen -
      Void Rush
    • Royal Venomshell -
      Venomous Spray
    • Hulking Warshell -
      Tremor Slam
    • Elder Shadeweaver -
      Umbral Weave

Boss Tips

E.D.N.A.

  • General Tips
    • Dispel
      Seismic Reverberation       right after the boss begins casting
      Seismic Smash       so your tank gets the damage reduction from
      Seismic Reverberation      .
  • Output Cds
    • Whenever you clear
      Volatile Spikes       with
      Refracting Beam       you need to have a Healing Cooldown active.
  • Personal/External
    • Whenever you clear
      Volatile Spikes       with
      Refracting Beam       ensure to have a defensive cooldown and both
      Protective Light       and
      Fade       active.

Skarmorak

  • General Tips
    • Whenever Void fragments spawn instantly soak one to gain
      Unstable Energy      . Extend the buff right before
      Fortified Shell      .
  • Output Cds
    • Rotate through your healing cooldown arsenal when the boss channels
      Void Discharge      .
  • Personal/External
    • Use your personal defensives when
      Void Discharge       happens.

Master Machinists Brokk and Dorlita

  • General Tips
    • Make sure to look around for safe vents to not get caught by surprise.
  • Output Cds
    • Whenever
      Exhaust Vents       occurs, you need to have multiple Holy Words ready.
  • Personal/External
    • Use
      Desperate Prayer       when
      Exhaust Vents       overlaps with
      Metal Splinters      .

Void Speaker Eirich

  • General Tips
    • Since Holy Priest lacks mobility preposition next to the portals to get rid of
      Void Corruption       as soon as possible.
  • Output Cds
    • This fight has a high constant HPS requirement so make sure you spread out your Cooldowns to have a constant stream of high HPS.
  • Personal/External
    • Ensure to have a personal defensive active when you still have a
      Void Corruption       when the boss casts
      Entropic Reckoning      .

Trash Tips

  • Important abilities to interrupt in this dungeon are:
    • Ghastly Voidsoul -
      Howling Fear
    • Void Bound Howler -
      Piercing Wail
  • Pay extra attention to these casts:
    • Void Bound Despoiler -
      Void Storm
    • Forge Loader -
      Molten Mortar
    • Rock Smasher -
      Smash Rock
    • Cursedforge Honor Guard -
      Shield Stampede
    • Cursedforge Stoneshaper -
      Earth Burst Totem
    • Earth Burst Totem casts
      Earth Burst       which needs to be killed before it goes off.

Boss Tips

Speaker Shadowcrown

  • General Tips
    • Dispel
      Burning Shadows       as fast as possible.
  • Output Cds
    • Whenever you dispel
      Burning Shadows       your party gets a DoT with a healing absorb.
  • Personal/External
    • There are no planned uses, use stuff freely when things go wrong.

Anub'ikkaj

  • General Tips
    • Make sure if you are targeted by
      Dark Orb       to not aim it into a wall, as if it does not travel for a long time you will wipe.
  • Output Cds
    • Shadowy Decay       happens every 41 seconds, so you have to alternate your healing cooldowns with your defensives and communicate that with your group. If you don't have either up this ability will kill you.
  • Personal/External
    • Rotate your personals to mitigate damage from
      Shadowy Decay      .

Rasha'nan

  • General Tips
    • Tell your group to not pick up
      Arathi Bomb       during
      Erosive Spray       cast to avoid unnecessary high damage overlap in Phase 1.
  • Output Cds
    • You need to heal through
      Erosive Spray       because people do need their defensive for when they are targeted with
      Spinneret's Strands      .
  • Personal/External
    • You cannot get targeted by
      Spinneret's Strands       as a healer so make sure to use your personals on
      Erosive Spray       instead.

Trash Tips

  • Important abilities to interrupt in this dungeon are:
    • Nightfall Shadowmage -
      Ensnaring Shadows
    • Nightfall Commander -
      Abyssal Howl
    • Nightfall Darkcaster -
      Tormenting Beam
  • Pay extra attention to these casts:
    • Ixkreten the Unbreakable -
      Terrifying Slam       and
      Abyssal Rot
    • Nightfall Dark Architect -
      Usher Reinforcements
    • Deathscreamer Iken'tak -
      Dark Orb       and
      Abyssal Rot
      • Watch out for players with
        Abyssal Rot         during
        Dark Orb         explosion.
    • Ascendant Vis'coxria -
      Shadowy Decay       and
      Abyssal Rot
      • Watch out for players with
        Abyssal Rot         during
        Shadowy Decay         cast.

Boss Tips

Ingra Maloch

  • General Tips
    • It is very easy to die on this boss if interrupts are not properly managed, ensure that during
      Embrace Darkness       no kick goes through as they will execute their target.
  • Output Cds
    • Save your healing cooldowns for when Ingra is protected by
      Embrace Darkness       as before there is no damage.
  • Personal/External
    • No planned uses, use stuff freely when things go wrong or you are low on healing.

Mistcaller

  • General Tips
    • Fear the fox spawned by
      Freeze Tag       to help your party.
  • Output Cds
    • Save your healing cooldowns for
      Guessing Game       as that is the only time your Group takes damage.
  • Personal/External
    • Rotate through your defensive arsenal while
      Guessing Game       is active.

Tred'ova

  • General Tips
    • Focus on not moving a lot whenever
      Acid Expulsion       happens to not kill a teammate later down the line.
  • Output Cds
    • Ensure to have multiple Holy Words ready for
      Consumption       as this is the only time your party takes heavy damage.
  • Personal/External
    • Use your defensives whenever you are focused as
      Marked Prey      .

Trash Tips

  • Important abilities to interrupt in this dungeon are:
    • Drust Harvester -
      Harvest Essence
    • Spinemaw Staghorn -
      Stimulate Resistance
  • Pay extra attention to these casts:
    • Drust Spiteclaw -
      Dying Breath
      • This debuffs enemies as well as players.
    • Tirnenn Villager -
      Overgrowth
    • Drust Boughbreaker -
      Furious Thrashing
      • Triggers at 50% HP of the Drust Boughbreaker. Make sure to have healing cooldowns ready for it.
    • Mistveil Defender -
      Mist Ward
    • Mistveil Stalker -
      Mistveil Bite
    • Mistveil Stinger -
      Anima Injection
      • Poison dispel.
    • Spinemaw Staghorn -
      Acid Nova

Boss Tips

Blightbone

  • General Tips
    • Use
      Psychic Scream       to disrupt the spawned adds.
    • Dispel the disease after each
      Heaving Retch       cast.
  • Output Cds
    • Use everything to maximize damage as there is no AoE damage on this boss.
  • Personal/External
    • Ensure to have both
      Protective Light       and
      Fade       active and have a defensive cooldown active whenever targeted by
      Heaving Retch      .

Amarth, The Harvester

  • General Tips
    • Be ready to use
      Shackle Undead       if
      Final Harvest       cast is about to finish and there are still some adds alive. As long as they are CCed as the cast finishes it will prevent them from exploding.
  • Output Cds
    • Save your healing cooldowns for after
      Final Harvest       is completed as that is the only time AoE damage happens.
  • Personal/External
    • Ensure to have a defensive active whenever your group runs out of interrupts and you are targeted by
      Necrotic Bolt      .

Surgeon Stitchflesh

  • General Tips
    • The most important part about this encounter is to hit the hook at the correct time. Use your
      Angelic Feathers       to help your party get into position.
  • Output Cds
    • Save your healing cooldowns for when multiple abominations are active as
      Festering Rot       does heavy group damage.
  • Personal/External
    • Ensure to have a defensive active whenever you are targeted with
      Stitchneedle      .

Nalthor the Rimebinder

  • General Tips
    • You can use
      Leap of Faith       to save
      Dark Exile       if you grip them directly after the
      Dark Exile       cast finished. Keep in mind they will still die when the duration of the debuff expires.
  • Output Cds
    • Save your Holy Words for
      Icebound Aegis       as this is the only time AoE damage happens.
  • Personal/External
    • Rotate through your defensive arsenal whenever
      Icebound Aegis       is active on the boss.

Trash Tips

  • Important abilities to interrupt in this dungeon are:
    • Corpse Harvester -
      Drain Fluids
    • Stitched Vanguard -
      Meat Shield
    • Skeletal Marauder -
      Rasping Scream
    • Corpse Collector -
      Goresplatter
  • Pay extra attention to these casts:
    • Zolramus Necromancer -
      Grim Fate
    • Skeletal Marauder -
      Gruesome Cleave
      • Fast frontal cast.
    • Flesh Crafter -
      Throw Cleaver
      • This spell also does damage to enemies and should be aimed at any enemy to deal extra damage.
        • Help with this by positioning the mobs in front of the Flesh Crafter.
    • Loyal Creation -
      Spine Crush
      • A big circle cast that can't be disrupted as it recasts until the cast is finished once.

Boss Tips

Chopper Redhook

  • General Tips
    • Look out for clutch
      Leap of Faiths       on players fixated with
      On the Hook      .
  • Output Cds
    • Save your healing cooldowns for when
      Gore Crash       happens to ensure nobody gets executed by a
      Molten Slug      .
  • Personal/External
    • Ensure to have a defensive active when targeted by
      Molten Slug       and
      Gore Crash       is about to happen.

Dread Captain Lockwood

  • Output Cds
    • Cycle through your healing cooldowns for every
      Fiery Ricochet      .
  • Personal/External
    • Ensure to have a personal defensive active for
      Fiery Ricochet      .

Hadal Darkfathom

  • General Tips
    • Ask for external sprints to dodge
      Tidal Surge       if your group can provide them.
  • Output Cds
    • Break Water       is the only damage event on this boss. Ensure people are always topped before this.
  • Personal/External
    • Rotate through your defensive arsenal whenever
      Break Water       happens and have both
      Protective Light       and
      Fade       active.

Viq'Goth

  • General Tips
    • Always have your group be spread to be able to instantly dispel a
      Putrid Waters      .
  • Output Cds
    • Spot heal
      Putrid Waters       whenever
      Slam       happens.
    • Preplan your
      Mass Dispel       casts so your group can position accordingly.
  • Personal/External
    • Whenever you tank
      Putrid Waters       for its duration ensure to have a defensive active.
    • Use
      Guardian Spirit       on
      Putrid Waters       targetes without defensives.

Trash Tips

  • Important abilities to interrupt in this dungeon are:
    • Ashvane Commander -
      Bolstering Shout
    • Bilge Rat Tempest -
      Choking Waters
    • Bilge Rat Pillager -
      Stinky Vomit
  • Pay extra attention to these casts:
    • Scrimshaw Enforcer -
      Slobber Knocker
      • Casted frontal cone that is hard to see.
    • Irontide Raider -
      Iron Hook       into
      Savage Tempest
    • Blacktar Bomber -
      Fire Bomb
    • Ashvane Commander -
      Azerite Charge
    • Irontide Powdershot -
      Molten Slug
    • Ashvane Spotter -
      Sighted Artillery
    • Bilge Rat Demolisher -
      Crushing Slam

Boss Tips

General Umbriss

  • General Tips
    • Ask for AoE sprints or
      Rescue       to dodge
      Shadow Breath       more efficiently.
  • Personal/External
    • Ensure to have both
      Protective Light       and
      Fade       active when
      Commanding Roar       happens.

Forgemaster Throngus

  • General Tips
    • Bait
      Fiery Cleave       to the nearest wall to save boss room space.
  • Output Cds
    • Save your healing cooldowns for whenever Throngus has his sword out, as that is the phase when heavy AoE damage happens.
  • Personal/External
    • Use
      Desperate Prayer       on every overlap of
      Molten Flurry       and
      Forge Swords      .

Drahga Shadowburner

  • General Tips
    • Use
      Leap of Faith       to help players fixated with
      Flaming Fixate      .
  • Output Cds
    • Ensure that people are at full health before every
      Twilight Buffet      .
  • Personal/External
    • Ensure to have both
      Protective Light       and
      Fade       and a defensive active when
      Twilight Buffet       happens.

Erudax, the Duke of Below

  • General Tips
    • Ask for AoE sprints or
      Rescue       whenever
      Shadow Gale       happens.
  • Output Cds
    • You have to heal through
      Void Surge       as people need their defensives to survive the overlap of
      Abyssal Corruption       and
      Shadow Wound      .

Trash Tips

  • Important abilities to interrupt in this dungeon are:
    • Twilight Earthcaller -
      Mass Tremor
    • Twilight Beguiler -
      Sear Mind
  • Pay extra attention to these casts:
    • Twilight Destroyer -
      Umbral Wind
      • You can LoS this cast.
    • Molten Giant -
      Molten Wake
      • Massive AoE damage on to the entire group.
    • Twilight Lavabender -
      Ascension       and
      Dark Eruption
      • Ascension         triggers at 50% HP and starts pulsing
        Scorching Heat         group damage. Save healing cooldowns for that.
    • Twilight Warlock -
      Enveloping Shadowflame
    • Twilight Enforcer -
      Ramping Rage
    • Mutated Hatchling -
      Shadow Wound
    • Faceless Corruptor -
      Corrupt       and
      Mind Piercer

Affixes

The Affix system got revamped going into The War Within Season 1 retiring most Affixes as well as introducing new kiss-curse ones while also changing on which key level these appear.

  • +2 Affixes -- Rotates on a weekly basis
    • Xal'atath's Bargain: Ascendant
    • Xal'atath's Bargain: Voidbound
    • Xal'atath's Bargain: Oblivion
    • Xal'atath's Bargain: Devour
  • +4 Affixes -- Alternates between each other on a weekly basis
    • Tyrannical
    • Fortified
  • +7 Affix
    • Challenger's Peril
  • +10 Affixes -- Alternates between each other on a weekly basis, is always the opposite of the +4 Affix
    • Tyrannical
    • Fortified
  • +12 Affix
    • Xal'atath's Guile       -- Replaces the +2 Affix

Following you get some useful tips for handling different Mythic+ Affixes as a Holy Priest.

  • Xal'atath's Bargain: Ascendant
    • Use
      Psychic Scream       or
      Mass Dispel       to interrupt as many orbs as possible.
  • Xal'atath's Bargain: Voidbound
    • There is nothing special you can do to help with this affix.
  • Xal'atath's Bargain: Oblivion
    • Keep an eye behind you and collect any orbs that fly into melee range. Make sure to intercept them before they hit any enemies.
  • Xal'atath's Bargain: Devour
    • You can remove all debuffs at once with
      Mass Dispel      . If
      Mass Dispel       is on cooldown make sure to instantly single dispel one healing absorb debuff!

Stat Priority

Patch 11.0.7 - The War Within
Holy Priest

Understand your secondary stat priority and the tertiary stats needed for optimal performance during Mythic+ dungeons as a Holy Priest. For more detailed information, visit the Stats and Attributes guide.

The conclusion here is that you want to equip the highest item level generally.

All secondary stats are affected by diminishing returns. Click here to learn more!

Tertiary

  • Avoidance - Reduces damage taken from AoE effects.
  • Leech - Returns a portion of your damage and healing done as healing to you. (Excludes self healing)
  • Speed - increases movement speed. (Does stack with other movement speed abilities)

The only time you should think about picking a lower item level is if it has Leech or Avoidance. Speed is nice to have, but you should generally ignore that stat.

Farmable Alternatives

Due to the way stat weights work for Holy Priests, there isn't a strict best-in-slot list. Although it is theoretically possible to obtain items with all the correct Tertiaries, doing so requires extraordinary luck or several human lifespans because of the weekly reset system in World of Warcraft.

Authors Note:

This list shows the best items for healing in Raids from all sources. Keep in mind that getting different tier pieces with Leech / Avoidance changes which off-piece is best for you. Likewise, any other non-trinket item with Leech / Avoidance replaces the one suggested here.

Below you are presented with a good list of farmable alternatives that are obtainable outside of WoWs weekly lockout system. While replaced in time as you progress, these offer immediate character power.

Trinkets

Below you can find active and passive alternatives to our recommended trinkets. Do note that some trinkets are better than others depending on the dungeon.

Active Trinket alternatives

  • Spymaster's Web
    • A strong On-Use Trinket that rewards precise planning. It takes 4 minutes to reach max stacks, so make sure to tie it to the important damage events instead of just using it on cooldown!

Passive Trinket alternatives

  • Empowering Crystal of Anub'ikkaj
    • A very strong stat stick, granting you a huge random secondary stat proc.
  • Ovi'nax's Mercurial Egg
    • Very interesting Trinket, that gives you a mix of main stat and your highest secondary. Use it when moving to the next pull to keep a good distribution.
  • Ara-Kara Sacbrood
    • Another very good stat stick that also deals a very minor amount of damage.

Embellishments

  • Darkmoon Sigil: Ascension
    • Very strong stat stick that gives you a high amount of a random secondary stat that changes every 8 seconds.
  • Writhing Armor Banding
    • Doubles the effect of your
      Darkmoon Sigil: Ascension      .

Remaining Sparks

  • Crafted items are 636 item level and regular items are 639 on max item level, therefore, it's not beneficial to equip crafted items outside of your 2x embellishments unless you don't have access to other high item level gear on that slot.

Addons

Patch 11.0.7 - The War Within
Holy Priest

Below, you see a screenshot of the author's User Interface for their Holy Priest, outlining which addons are used and how they are utilized in Mythic+ Dungeons to make your life easier.

Addons

  • OmniCD --- Party CD Tracker
    • Addon to track your party members' Cooldowns, mandatory for M+
  • ElvUI / BetterBlizzFrames --- Party/Raidframe Addon
    • Addon to replace your Unitframes and other UI Elements with a more clean look. Takes quite some time to configure but there are plenty of pre-done profiles that you can easily import and check out.
    • Alternatively, you can also use BetterBlizzFrames if you want to not spend hours configuring this.
  • WeakAuras --- Jack of all trades
    • WeakAura allows players to create and customize graphical displays of game information. These displays, known as "auras" can show various aspects such as buffs, debuffs, cooldowns, health, and other important events.
  • Plater --- Nameplate Addon
    • Plater is a nameplate addon with an extraordinary amount of settings, out of the box debuff tracking, threat coloring, and support for scripting similar to WeakAuras + the WeakAuras-Companion for Mod/Script/Profile updates.
  • Details --- Damage Meter
    • Shows you Damage/Healing throughout the dungeon

WeakAuras

These WeakAuras are recommended for optimal performance in Mythic+ dungeons as a Holy Priest.

Power Word: Life Glow

Glows your frame when Power Word: Life is useable

Stamina Tracker

Shows an icon when you need to buff stamina

Power Infusion Handler

Notifies you when someone requests PI of you

Changes this Patch

Patch 11.0.7 - The War Within
Holy Priest

Patch 11.0.1

  • Priest
    • All talent trees have had many talents move locations or have had their pathing updated.
    • New Talent: Cauterizing Shadows When your Shadow Word: Pain or Purge the Wicked expires or is refreshed with less than 5 seconds remaining, a nearby ally within 40 yards is healed.
    • New Talent: Phantom Reach Increases the range of most spells by 15%.
    • Manipulation has been redesigned Now causes you to take 1%/2% less damage from targets affected by Shadow Word: Pain, Purge the Wicked, or Holy Fire.
    • Power Word: Life healing increased by 15%.
    • Void Tendrils now root targets for 15 seconds (was 20 seconds).
    • Power Word: Shield and Luminous Barrier's absorb values now have a 5% variance, like other healing spells.
    • The following talents have been removed:
      • Mindgames (moved to PvP talents)
      • Shattered Perceptions
  • Holy
    • Divine Hymn healing increased by 400%.
    • Divine Hymn now decreases its healing beyond 5 targets.

Patch 11.0.2

  • Priest
    • Flash Heal healing increased by 20%.
    • Power Word: Shield absorb amount increased by 20%.
    • Power Word: Life healing increased by 20%.
    • Cauterizing Shadows healing increased by 60%.
    • Healing done from Void Shift to the Priests ally is now capped at twice the Priests Health.
    • From Darkness Comes Light now increases the healing of Flash Heal by 3% (was 1%), and stacks up to 20 times (was 50).
    • Prayer of Mending is now removed from all allies except for the last ally that received one from the Priest when a raid encounter begins.
    • Fixed an issue causing Holy Nova to not benefit from Phantom Reach.
    • Fixed an issue causing Halo to damage enemies out of combat.
    • Updated the visuals and animations for Void Shift.
    • Fixed an issue causing Divine Images teleport to fail on transports.
    • Added a counter to the Heal spell for tracking the status of Lightweaver.
    • The following talents are now 1 point:Manipulation
      • Surge of Light
  • Holy
    • All damage increased by 10%.
    • Heal healing increased by 44%.
    • Flash Heal healing increased by 20%.
    • Prayer of Healing healing increased by 30%.
    • Circle of Healing healing increased by 30%.
    • Holy Word: Serenity healing increased by 20%.
    • Divine Images Healing Light spell healing increased by 20%.
    • Healing Chorus now increases the healing done by Circle of Healing by 3% (was 5%).
    • Lightweaver now increases Heal healing by 25% (was 15%).
    • Fixed an issue causing the values for Gales of Song to be incorrect.
    • Trail of Light is now a 1-point talent.

Patch 11.0.5

  • Priest
    • Power Word: Fortitude now costs 1% base mana (was 4%).
  • Holy
    • From Darkness Comes Light has been updated to also trigger from Holy Fire damage.
  • Archon
    • Sustained Potency has been updated It now also pauses the duration of Apotheosis, Dark Ascension, or Voidform for up to 20 seconds while out of combat or affected by a loss of control effect.
    • Fixed an issue causing Cyclone and similar effects to prevent Halos from Power Surge from firing.
    • Fixed an issue causing Halo to not be castable during Divine Ascension.

Patch 11.0.7

  • Priest
    • Holy
      • Flash Heal healing increased by 15%.
      • Holy Fire damage increased by 15%.
